                <div class="tab-content">
                    <div class="tab-pane active" id="tab-script">
                        <div class="js-script-content-wrapper top-margin-script markdown-content">
                                                                                        <a href="https://github.com/knpuniversity/symfony2-rest/edit/master/knpu/episode1/form-post.md" target="_blank" class="btn btn-default btn-circle pull-right js-tooltip" title="Edit on GitHub"><span class="fa fa-pencil"></span></a>
                                                                    <p>So what's different between this API controller and one that handles
an HTML form submit? Really, not much. The biggest difference is that an
HTML form sends us POST parameters and an API sends us a JSON string. But once
we decode the JSON, both give us an array of submitted data. Then, everything
is the same: create a Programmer object and update it with the submitted
data. And you know who does this kind of work really well? Bernhard Schussek err
Symfony forms!</p>
<p>Create a new directory called <code>Form/</code> and inside of that, a new class called
<code>ProgrammerType</code>. I'll quickly make this into a form type by extending
<code>AbstractType</code> and implementing the <code>getName()</code> method - just return,
how about, <code>programmer</code>.</p>
<p>Now, override the two methods we <em>really</em> care about - <code>setDefaultOptions()</code>
and <code>buildForm()</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="1676cfb7f6">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
            <span class="fa fa-clipboard js-activate-clipboard" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Copy Code" data-placement="top"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="info">
                        <span class="js-expand-all" data-range="1-43" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Show All Lines" data-placement="top">
                <i class="fa fa-expand js-icon-load-more"></i>
                <i class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin js-icon-loading"></i>
            </span>
            
            43 lines <span class="meta-divider"></span> <span title="src/AppBundle/Form/ProgrammerType.php">src/AppBundle/Form/ProgrammerType.php</span>
        </div>
    </div>
    <table class="hljs code-block-table">
        <tbody class="js-tr-container">
                <tr>
                    <td class="line-number line-number-displayed" data-line-number-displayed="1"></td>
            <td class="blob-code"><span class="hljs-meta">&lt;?php</span></td>
            </tr>
    <tr>
                    <td class="line-number line-number-displayed" data-line-number-displayed="2"></td>
            <td class="blob-code"></td>
