</p>
<p>Ok, this is really cool because it turns out that when we call <code>$form-&gt;handleRequest()</code>,
all <em>it</em> does is finds the form's POST parameters array and then passes that
to <code>$form-&gt;submit()</code>. With <code>$form-&gt;submit()</code>, you're doing the same thing
as normal, but working more directly with the form.</p>
<p>And that's all the code you need! So let's try it:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">php testing.php</div></code></pre>
<p>Yep! The server seems confident that still worked. That's all
I need to hear!</p>
<h2 id="creating-a-resource-201-status-code">Creating a Resource? 201 Status Code <a class="headerlink" href="form-post#creating-a-resource-201-status-code" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
