<h2 id="creating-a-resource-location-header">Creating a Resource? Location Header <a class="headerlink" href="form-post#creating-a-resource-location-header" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Second, when you create a resource, best-practices say that you should set
a <code>Location</code> header on the response. Set the <code>new Response</code> line to a
<code>$response</code> variable and then add the header with <code>$response-&gt;headers-&gt;set()</code>.
The value should be the URL to the new resource... buuuut we don't have an
endpoint to view one Programmer yet, so let's fake it:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="dfe7db9425">
