	                        <div id="dsq-comment-message-2715887051" class="dsq-comment-message">
	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-2715887051" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>in Symfony 3.0.6, $form-&gt;submit doesn't seem to validate a collection of forms.<br>Let's say you have an order which has some information and also an array of lines (BlanketOrderLine object).<br>BlanketOrderLineType is the form type for BlanketOrderLine .<br>Parent form is validated but not the BlanketOrderLineType ....</p><p>$builder<br>-&gt;add('lines', CollectionType::class,</p><p>  array('entry_type' =&gt; BlanketOrderLineType::class,<br>    'label' =&gt; false,<br>    'allow_add' =&gt; true,<br>    'allow_delete' =&gt; true,<br>    'prototype' =&gt; false,<br>    'required' =&gt; true,<br>    'by_reference' =&gt; false,<br>    'entry_options' =&gt; array('constraints' =&gt; [new Assert\Valid()])<br>    ));</p><p>Any idea why?</p>
