	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-2074975715" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>You got it :). submit() calls the setters (after the normal data transformations of the form). And yes, you'd absolutely be able to do a $form-&gt;isValid() - it's something we'll do in the next episode (recording now) to return a nice response with validation errors.</p>
